    "body": "The ``#ifdef PYPY_VERSION`` leaves ``CYTHON_USE_ASYNC_SLOTS`` always undefined, even on PyPy3.  This miscompiles extensions that try to define types with e.g. an ``am_await`` slot.  For example, uvloop complains with:\r\n\r\n```\r\nuvloop/loop.c: At top level:\r\nuvloop/loop.c:121550:8: error: unknown type name '__Pyx_PyAsyncMethodsStruct'\r\n static __Pyx_PyAsyncMethodsStruct __pyx_tp_as_async_BaseFuture = {\r\n        ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\r\n```\r\n\r\nDefining ``CYTHON_USE_ASYNC_SLOTS`` to be ``1`` on PyPy3 gets rid of this particular error (there are others).",
